<!--
  Personal/global CLAUDE.md — copy to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md

  Source: /engineering/claude-code-best-practices — Claude Code reads
  ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md on every session, *in addition to* the project's
  CLAUDE.md. Use it for preferences that hold across all your projects.

  Three to five lines is plenty. Every token here costs attention in every
  session, regardless of which project you're in. Do not pad to "feel
  complete" — that's the documented anti-pattern.
-->

- Commits in <TODO English | Spanish>, imperative mood, no emojis.
- Prefer <TODO TypeScript over JavaScript | Python over Bash | Rust over Go> when both are reasonable.
- Do NOT run unrequested refactors or "drive-by" cleanups.
- For shell snippets, default to <TODO POSIX bash | PowerShell> unless the project says otherwise.
- When uncertain about a path or convention, ask before guessing.
